    "response": "To compute the **sample standard deviation** of the dataset:\n\n$$\n\\{1, 12, -17, -3, -11, -5\\}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 1: Find the mean (average)\n\n$$\n\\text{Mean} = \\frac{1 + 12 + (-17) + (-3) + (-11) + (-5)}{6}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{1 + 12 - 17 - 3 - 11 - 5}{6} = \\frac{-19}{6} \\approx -3.1667\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 2: Subtract the mean from each value and square the result\n\n$$\n\\begin{align*}\n(1 - (-3.1667))^2 &= (4.1667)^2 \\approx 17.3611 \\\\\n(12 - (-3.1667))^2 &= (15.1667)^2 \\approx 229.7778 \\\\\n(-17 - (-3.1667))^2 &= (-13.8333)^2 \\approx 191.3778 \\\\\n(-3 - (-3.1667))^2 &= (0.1667)^2 \\approx 0.0278 \\\\\n(-11 - (-3.1667))^2 &= (-7.8333)^2 \\approx 61.3778 \\\\\n(-5 - (-3.1667))^2 &= (-1.8333)^2 \\approx 3.3611 \\\\\n\\end{align*}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 3: Sum the squared differences\n\n$$\n17.3611 + 229.7778 + 191.3778 + 0.0278 + 61.3778 + 3.3611 \\approx 492.4926\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 4: Divide by $n - 1$ (sample variance)\n\n$$\n\\text{Sample variance} = \\frac{492.4926}{6 - 1} = \\frac{492.4926}{5"
